<subSubSection pageNumber="871" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="871">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="871">
Note: 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Galeopsis" higherTaxonomySource="IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="hirsuta">Galeopsis hirsuta</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
was transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Sideritis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="871">Sideritis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 1759 (as 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Stachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ocymastrum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="871">S. ocymastrum</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
because of the existence of 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1753))" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Sideritis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="871">Sideritis hirsuta</emphasis>
L. (1753))
</taxonomicName>
, and then appeared as 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1763" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Stachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="871">Stachys hirta</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
in 1763. The use of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“hirta”">&quot;hirta&quot;</normalizedToken>
may originally have been an error for 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“hirsuta”">&quot;hirsuta&quot;</normalizedToken>
(as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Galeopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="871">G. hirsuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is included in its synonymy), but as Linnaeus continued to use 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“hirta”">&quot;hirta&quot;</normalizedToken>
in later works (Linnaeus 1767: 395; 1774: 447), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1763" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Stachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="871">Stachys hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is treated as illegitimate.
</paragraph>
